data.title: Australia National Football Team Color Codes Hex, RGB, and CMYK
data.meta_description: Australia National Football Team Color Codes HTML Hex, RGB, PANTONE and CMYK Color Values for digital or print projects where you need to match a specific color and require the Australia National Football Team Color Codes. Search for other teams and colors on Team Color Codes
data.text:
The Australia National Football Team colors are green and gold. The Australia National Football Team team colors in Hex, RGB, and CMYK can be found below. The Australia National Football Team represents Australia internationally. Group rivals of Australia in the Qatar 2022 FIFA World Cup include France, Denmark, and Tunisia.

The primary colors of the Australia National Football Team can be found in the table below.

The Australia 2022 FIFA World Cup team Pantone colors are PMS 348 C for green and PMS 116 C for gold.

The green Pantone color of the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

PMS 348 C

The gold Pantone color of the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

PMS 116 C

The Australia National Football Team colors HEX codes are #00843D for green and #FFCD00 for gold.

The green HEX color code for the Australia soccer team can be found below.

#00843D

The gold HEX colour code for the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

#FFCD00

The Australia National Football Team colors RGB codes are (0, 132, 61) for green and (255, 205, 0) for gold colour.

The green RGB color code for the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

(0, 132, 61)

The gold RGB colour code for the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

(255, 205, 0)

The Australia National Football Team colors CMYK codes are (100, 0, 54, 48) for green and (0, 20, 100, 0) for gold color.

The green CMYK color code for the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

(100, 0, 54, 48)

The gold CMYK colour code for the Australia National Football Team can be found below.

(0, 20, 100, 0)

The Australia National Football Team logo colors are green and gold. The green color code for the Australia National Football Team logo is Pantone: PMS 348 C, Hex Color: #00843D, RGB: (0, 132, 61), CMYK: (100, 0, 54, 48). The gold color code for the Australia National Football Team logo is Pantone: PMS 116 C, Hex Color: #FFCD00, RGB: (255, 205, 0), CMYK: (0, 20, 100, 0).

The Australia National Football Team logo has green and gold colors and a badge-shaped emblem with the Australian coat of arms at its center. The Australia National Football Team logo meaning symbolizes the well-known entities of Australia, the country it represents.

The Australia National Football Team logo colours can be found in an image format below.

The Australia National Football Team logo font is a custom typeface. The Australia National Football Team font is used for jersey lettering, player names, numbers, team logo, branding, and merchandise.
